text: Panimalar Engineering College governed by JAISAKTHI Educational Trust aims at imparting quality engineering and management education for the aspiring youth. The College is accredited by National Board of Accreditation (NBA), New Delhi, approved by All India Council for Technical Education (AICTE) and recognized by UGC with 12(B) & 2(f) status. The college is located near Poonamallee, Chennai, and is well connected by road covering Chennai, Kancheepuram and Thiruvallur districts.

The Trust started Panimalar Engineering College in the year 2000 in accordance with the general policy of the Government of Tamil Nadu. The policy emphasizes giving high priority to meet the demand for trained engineers for various industrial and development projects in the state of Tamil Nadu and the rest of India.

Vision of the Institute: To transform the budding engineers into academically excellent, highly intellectual and self disciplined engineering graduates to mould them as good citizens with the spirit of integrity and morality that would cater to the needs of our nation.

Mission of the Institute: To impart quality education with high standards of excellence in engineering and technology and to provide an excellent infrastructure in a serene and conducive atmosphere that would motivate the students in their pursuit of knowledge.

Quality Policy: The Institution strives to provide high quality education and training in Engineering, Science and Management for aspiring youth in the growth of engineering profession and industry by providing and maintaining good learning environment and inculcating professional ethics, standards and morale through student career and personality development programs.

Our Campus: This sprawling campus provides a holistic education in an ambience that makes no compromise on discipline, dedication and commitment. It offers state of the art facilities and ensures students turn out academically brilliant, morally upright and empowered individuals.

Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning has been established in the year 2022 and is recognized by AICTE. Artificial Intelligence specialization creates engineers who can build solutions with intelligence similar to humans.

Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning conducts co-curricular activities such as guest lectures, seminars, training programs and workshops. Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning also organizes industrial visits to help students update their knowledge.

An exclusive Training and Placement cell functions within Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning to provide continuous training and placement assistance to students during their course of study. Students are trained by internal trainers and industry experts with various training partners to improve their employability skills such as soft skills, technical skills, analytical skills and logical skills. Students are encouraged to organize and participate in events like paper presentations, technical symposia and project presentations to enhance innovative thinking and managerial skills.

Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning focuses on emerging digital technologies where data and machine learning drive global companies such as Facebook, Google and Uber. Machine learning market size has been steadily growing and is a type of data mining that allows computers to learn from experience.
Until the 1960s Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning were more or less synonymous, but thereafter they diverged and now they are widespread across the tech industry, mass media and academia.

Data scientists and machine learning engineers are among the top-ranked jobs globally. Professionals with expertise in data science and machine learning are highly sought after by technology and finance organizations.

The Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning course dives deep into foundational and advanced concepts of data science and machine learning to enable students to devise practical solutions in real-world contexts.

Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning provides state-of-the-art computing facilities to students enabling them to stay ahead. Students are exposed to opportunities such as in-plant training, internships and workshops during their course of study.

Vision of Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning: To be a center of excellence in the field of Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning applications through appropriate use and diffusion of emerging techniques.

Mission of Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning: To develop students with strong capabilities in Artificial Intelligence by continuously enhancing teaching and learning with state-of-the-art technologies.

Mission of Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning: To provide high-quality, value-based education to gain competence in Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning in terms of research and innovation activities.
Mission of Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning: To implement engineering solutions for the benefit of society by the use of Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning.

Dr. B. Anni Princy M.E., Ph.D., is Professor and Head of Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning. She has 28 years of teaching experience. She completed her M.E. in Computer Science and Engineering in 2004 and Ph.D. in Computer Science and Engineering in 2015 from Sathyabama University, Chennai.

Dr. B. Anni Princy has published more than 50 articles in reputed national and international journals and holds 6 patents. Her areas of interest include Software Reliability Engineering, Networking and Machine Learning. She received Rs. 7,85,000 from AICTE for MODROB and is affiliated with IEEE and the Computer Society of India (CSI).

Dr. B. Anni Princy received the Inspiring Senior Faculty Award from Advanced Materials & Applications, an international peer-reviewed journal published by Madras Journal Series Pvt Ltd. She received the Best Teacher Award in 2007-2008 at Panimalar Engineering College and a Certificate of Appreciation for guiding teams in the IEEE Xtreme 11.0 programming competition held on 14th October 2017 with 8,300 participants.

The Assistant Professors in Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning are Mr. Nagaraj J, Mr. Muthu V, Mrs. Vanipriya B, Mrs. Pandi Kumari M R, Mrs. Saranya A, Mrs. Bharani M, Mr. Ezhilvendan M, Mrs. Ramathilagam A, Mr. Rizwan Basha A, Mrs. Thamizharasi K, Ms. Alamelu R, Mr. Venkatesan R, Mr. Akash S D, Ms. Derisha Mahil, Ms. Meenakshi L, Ms. Hashini S, Mr. Thiyagarajan C, Mrs. Venitha E, Mrs. Saranya V, Mr. Rajasekaran S, Mrs. Saranya K and Mrs. Kiruthika S.

Panimalar Engineering Institution provides 24/7 dedicated internet access with a 1500 Mbps 1:1 leased line connection, including 1000 Mbps from Tata Teleservices Ltd and 500 Mbps from Reliance Jio. All departments are equipped with internet connectivity to support academic and research activities.

Panimalar Engineering Institution has more than 4000 desktop PCs and laptops across various academic blocks connected through a fibre optic backbone. Internet access is provided to all systems on campus.

Panimalar Engineering Institution maintains sufficient licensed software as per curriculum requirements. Laboratories are equipped with licensed and open-source software to support lab sessions, research, training and certification programs. While most systems operate on open-source technologies, selected proprietary software is installed in specific labs to provide exposure to advanced technologies.

Panimalar Engineering Institution offers free 24/7 Wi-Fi access across the campus including placement hub, hostels, seminar halls and auditorium. The campus intranet provides essential information such as test schedules, timetables, examination schedules and campus updates.

Panimalar Engineering Institution has deployed Seqrite firewall integrated with antivirus and anti-malware solutions to ensure network and endpoint security. The system supports academic and administrative operations while maintaining a secure campus environment.

Panimalar Engineering Institution has established AICTE Idea Lab, Pride Centre, LIR Digital, Incubation Centre, Entrepreneurship Development Cell (EDC) and Centre of Excellence to promote innovation, skill development and entrepreneurship. These centres provide hands-on experience, industry exposure and mentorship in emerging technologies.

Seminar halls and smart classrooms at Panimalar Engineering Institution are equipped with interactive panels and smartboards. All laboratories have LCD projectors to support effective presentations and learning.

Panimalar Engineering Institution uses an ERP platform to streamline academic and administrative functions including Controller of Examinations, Library Management System and Student-Faculty Management System. The ERP enhances productivity and supports efficient institutional operations.

Panimalar Engineering Institution utilizes Google Workspace, Moodle and Microsoft Teams as part of its Learning Management System to facilitate communication, course delivery and collaboration between faculty and students.

Panimalar Engineering Institution uses Iamneo PAT Platform, Coders Forum Leader Board, Globarena and Aptis for technical and English language assessments. As an authorized Pearson VUE centre, the institution conducts globally recognized certification examinations.
The library at Panimalar Engineering Institution is equipped with barcode scanners for book issuance, returns and tracking the entry and exit of students and faculty.

All IT-related activities at Panimalar Engineering Institution including network management, hardware, software, interactive panels, projectors, UPS and IT maintenance are handled by the Technical Support Team.

Panimalar Engineering Institution operates a fleet of 170 buses to transport students and staff from various parts of the city and surrounding areas to the campus and back home. Transport facilities are arranged for every student to ensure punctuality and safe commuting.

In addition to regular scheduled trips, the transport facility at Panimalar Engineering Institution is extended for special coaching classes, placement and training sessions, industrial visits, hospital visits and NSS camps conducted beyond regular college hours.

Panimalar Engineering Institution provides a well-maintained mess facility to offer a congenial and homely atmosphere for students and staff. Many students from across Tamil Nadu stay in the hostel, and the mess ensures nutritious, delicious and wholesome food is served regularly.

The mess at Panimalar Engineering Institution is well ventilated, pest-free and equipped with marble seating arrangements. Separate rows are maintained for students and staff members, and clean stainless steel utensils are used to serve fresh food at stipulated times.
The college mess has a total area of 2,45,730 sq. ft. with a seating capacity of 6,800 persons. The dining hall spans 1,52,700 sq. ft., with separate seating for vegetarians and non-vegetarians.

The mess kitchen at Panimalar Engineering Institution covers 58,500 sq. ft. and is equipped with ultra-modern facilities including boilers, cookers and steam cookers. Separate cooking areas are maintained for vegetarian and non-vegetarian food, along with dedicated rooms for cylinders, storage, sweets, ice creams, vessels and staff workers.

Panimalar Engineering Institution provides a wholesome campus life combining education and enjoyment. The campus is self-sufficient, offering comprehensive facilities so that students do not need to leave the premises for essential services. The hostel facilities aim to create a comfortable and homely environment for students.

Panimalar Engineering Institution offers separate hostel facilities for boys and girls. Students are provided with spacious rooms equipped with attached bathrooms and running hot and cold water. The campus also includes large playgrounds and sports facilities for volleyball, basketball, shuttle, ball badminton and other outdoor games.

The Gents Hostel at Panimalar Engineering Institution accommodates over 1,600 students across 4,39,501 sq. ft. With four hostels containing 418 rooms, it houses up to 1,672 students from various departments. Rooms are furnished with cots, cupboards, chairs, attached bathrooms and hot and cold water. Additional facilities include Wi-Fi, computer center, gym, yoga hall, playground, medical services, beauty parlor, recreational room and treated drinking water.

The Ladies Hostel at Panimalar Engineering Institution accommodates over 1,000 students within 3,11,518 sq. ft. With three hostels providing 274 rooms, it can house up to 1,088 students from various departments. Each room includes cots, cupboards, chairs, attached bathrooms and hot and cold water. Facilities include Wi-Fi, computer center, gym, yoga hall, playground, medical services, beauty parlor, recreational room and treated drinking water.
